tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE client_portfolio (
    client_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    client_name VARCHAR(255),
    portfolio_url VARCHAR(255),
    shoot_schedule TIMESTAMP,
    image_license_agreement TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE Photoshoot_Schedules (
    schedule_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    client_id INT REFERENCES Client_Portfolios(client_id),
    shoot_date TIMESTAMP,
    photographer VARCHAR,
    location VARCHAR
);

CREATE TABLE client_portfolios (
 client_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 client_name VARCHAR(255),
 client_email VARCHAR(255),
 portfolio_desc TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE photoshoot_schedules (
 schedule_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 client_id INT,
 date DATE,
 start_time TIME,
 end_time TIME
)

CREATE TABLE image_licensing_agreements (
 agreement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 client_id INT,
 agreement_date DATE,
 agreement_desc TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE PhotoshootSchedules (
  schedule_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  client_id INT REFERENCES ClientPortfolios(client_id),
  photoshoot_date DATE,
  photoshoot_time TIME,
  location VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE ImageLicenses (
  license_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  client_id INT REFERENCES ClientPortfolios(client_id),
  license_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  license_start_date DATE,
  license_end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE StockImages (
  image_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  image_path VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  license_id INT REFERENCES ImageLicenses(license_id),
  photographer_name VARCHAR(255),
  upload_date DATE
);
